  "texts": [
    "The multi-round conversations could be significantly more diverse than single-round QA, and may have multiple acceptable answers.",
    "We wish to evaluate it fairly and faithfully in the future when our OptLLM is fully deployed.",
    "As for single-round QA, it should be noted that different formulas can lead to the same solution, e.g., adding a redundant constraint x ≥ 10 to an existing one x ≥ 20 will not affect the solution but x ≥ 10 may have not been mentioned by the problem description.",
    "Thus, evaluating the model by the solver results may overlook the mistakes in formulas, and we propose to evaluate the model by accuracy in formula generation.",
    "The model is considered correct on one sample only when all the variables, objective and constraints it generates matches exactly with the ground truth on that sample."
  ],
